# Repo Evolution Pipeline — Project Walkthrough

## What It Does

This is a **multi-agent AI pipeline** that scans your GitHub repos (org: `mk-knight23`) and automatically generates **improved mobile app versions** on GitLab (`mk-knight23-mobile`). It reads source code, understands the app's purpose, designs a mobile architecture, generates production-ready code (Expo/React Native/Flutter/Ionic), attaches CI/CD, and pushes everything to GitLab — fully automated.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph "Entry Points"
        CLI["CLI\npython -m pipeline"]
        API["FastAPI\nuvicorn api.main:app"]
    end

    subgraph "Orchestration"
        ORCH["PipelineOrchestrator\n(async, batched, concurrent)"]
        MON["PipelineMonitor\n(progress, timing, reports)"]
    end

    subgraph "6-Stage Agent Pipeline"
        S1["1. Scanner\nClone & extract source files"]
        S2["2. Analyzer\nLLM deep/shallow analysis"]
        S3["3. Architect\nFramework & navigation design"]
        S4["4. CodeGen\nGenerate full mobile app code"]
        S5["5. Quality Gates\n15 automated checks"]
        S6["6. Pusher\nCreate GitLab repo & push"]
    end

    CLI --> ORCH
    API --> ORCH
    ORCH --> S1 --> S2 --> S3 --> S4 --> S5 --> S6
    ORCH --> MON
```

---

## Two Parallel Systems

The project has **two versions of the pipeline** that coexist:

| | **V1 (LangGraph)** | **V2 (Orchestrator)** |
|---|---|---|
| **Location** | `graph/` + `agents/` | [pipeline/](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/api/main.py#47-54) |
| **Execution** | LangGraph `StateGraph` | Async [PipelineOrchestrator](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/orchestrator.py#32-245) |
| **Entry** | [api/main.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/api/main.py) (FastAPI) | [pipeline/__main__.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/__main__.py) (CLI) |
| **State** | [PipelineState](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/graph/state.py#50-71) (TypedDict) | [RepoEvolutionState](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/models.py#160-200) (Pydantic) |
| **Features** | Conditional routing, skip logic | Batching, concurrency, retries, monitoring, quality gates |

**V2 ([pipeline/](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/api/main.py#47-54)) is the more complete and production-ready system.** V1 is the original LangGraph prototype.

---

## Data Flow (V2 Pipeline)

### State Object: [RepoEvolutionState](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/models.py#L160-L200)

Each repo flows through as a single [RepoEvolutionState](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/models.py#160-200) that accumulates data:

```
RepoEvolutionState
├── repo_name, github_url           # Identity
├── source_files: {path → content}  # Raw source from GitHub
├── manifest: RepoManifest          # Metadata extraction
├── deep_analysis: DeepAnalysis     # LLM component analysis
├── design_brief: DesignBrief       # App purpose/UX summary
├── architecture: MobileArchitecture # Framework + screens + nav
├── generated_files: {path → code}  # Output mobile code
├── generation_result: GenerationResult # Quality + GitLab URL
└── stage, errors, retry_count      # Control flow
```

### Stage-by-Stage Breakdown

**Stage 1 — Scanner** ([scanner.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/scanner.py))
- Clones the GitHub repo to `/tmp/repo-evolution/source/`
- Filters out `node_modules`, `.git`, [build](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/architect.py#161-179) etc.
- Extracts source files (`.ts`, `.tsx`, `.js`, [.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/api/main.py), etc.) up to a 500K char budget
- Falls back to GitHub REST API if clone fails

**Stage 2 — Analyzer** ([analyzer.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/analyzer.py))
- **Deep analysis** (when source files available): Sends condensed source to Claude Sonnet → gets component breakdown, pages, API calls, data models, state shape
- **Shallow analysis** (metadata only): Uses Claude Haiku → gets [DesignBrief](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/graph/state.py#23-30) with purpose, features, UX flow
- Includes fallback [_fallback_design_brief()](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/analyzer.py#209-246) if LLM fails entirely

**Stage 3 — Architect** ([architect.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/architect.py))
- Deterministic framework selection based on category:

  | Category | Framework | Navigation | State Mgmt |
  |---|---|---|---|
  | Portfolio | Expo | Tab | Zustand |
  | Webapp | React Native | Hybrid | Zustand |
  | Game | Flutter | Stack | Riverpod |
  | Tool | Expo | Drawer | Zustand |

- Builds [ScreenSpec](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/models.py#117-126) list from deep analysis routes or infers from features
- Designs navigation, dependencies, and design tokens

**Stage 4 — CodeGen** ([codegen.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/codegen.py) — 959 lines, largest file)
- Generates **complete app scaffolding**:
  - Config files (`package.json`/`pubspec.yaml`, `tsconfig.json`, `app.json`)
  - Navigation (Expo Router layouts, RN Navigator, Flutter go_router)
  - Screens (LLM-generated from source when available, template fallback)
  - Shared components (Loading, ErrorBoundary, Card, Header)
  - State store (Zustand/Riverpod/Pinia)
  - API service layer
  - TypeScript types
  - README + ARCHITECTURE.md
- Uses Claude Sonnet for screen generation, templates for everything else

**Stage 5 — Quality Gates** ([gates.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/quality/gates.py))

15 automated checks, scoring 0–100:

| # | Gate | Checks |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Project structure | Required dirs/files exist |
| 2 | Config validity | package.json/pubspec parseable |
| 3 | Minimum screens | ≥ 3 screen files |
| 4 | Navigation connects | All screens linked |
| 5 | CI YAML | Valid `.gitlab-ci.yml` |
| 6 | README | Exists, > 50 lines |
| 7 | Architecture docs | ARCHITECTURE.md exists |
| 8 | Ancestor link | GitHub source URL referenced |
| 9 | No secrets | No hardcoded API keys |
| 10 | TypeScript quality | Proper typing, no `any` abuse |
| 11 | Accessibility | `accessibilityLabel` present |
| 12 | Offline support | Caching patterns present |
| 13 | Error handling | try/catch in components |
| 14 | No placeholders | No TODO/Lorem ipsum |
| 15 | Design tokens | Theme/colors file exists |

**Stage 6 — Pusher** ([pusher.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/pusher.py))
- Creates or finds GitLab project (name format: `{repo}-mobile-{framework}`)
- Attaches CI/CD template ([ci_templates.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/agents/ci_templates.py) — Expo/RN/Flutter/Ionic)
- Batch commits files (150 per commit, GitLab API limit)
- Configures project settings, topics, creates `develop` branch

---

## Configuration

[config.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/config.py) — All settings centralized:

- **LLM**: Claude Sonnet 4.5 (heavy/analysis) + Haiku 4.5 (light/scanning), temp 0.1–0.3
- **Concurrency**: batch size 5, max concurrent 3, max retries 3
- **Limits**: 80K char source limit, 8 screens max, 50K file size max
- **Secrets**: All from env vars, never hardcoded

---

## LLM Layer

[llm.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/llm.py) provides:
- [create_llm()](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/llm.py#122-147) — Factory for `ChatAnthropic` instances
- [invoke_with_retry()](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/llm.py#149-202) — Async with exponential backoff (5s, 15s, 30s)
- [extract_json()](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/llm.py#83-118) — Robust JSON extraction (handles `<think>` blocks, code fences, regex fallback)
- [CostTracker](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/core/llm.py#34-75) — Per-model, per-stage cost tracking

---

## Monitoring

[dashboard.py](file:///Users/mkazi/GitLab%20Mobile%20/repo-evolution-pipeline/pipeline/monitoring/dashboard.py) — Real-time terminal dashboard with:
- Progress bars, stage timing, ANSI-colored output
- Per-repo status tracking (completed/failed/skipped)
- Final summary report with cost breakdown
- State persistence to `data/` directory
- Health checks for all dependencies (GitHub, GitLab, Anthropic, Supabase)

---

## How to Run

```bash
# Full pipeline on manifests file
python -m pipeline run --manifests data/manifests.json

# Single repo
python -m pipeline run-single --repo mk-knight23/my-repo --category webapp

# Health check
python -m pipeline health

# Quality check on existing files
python -m pipeline quality --files-dir ./output

# FastAPI server (V1 LangGraph path)
uvicorn api.main:app --reload
```

